cs.SY, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.GR 

The paper deals with the optimization of UAV path planning for monitoring and intervention of dynamic spreading processes such as wildfires. It utilizes the properties of positive systems and value functions to provide scalable algorithms for surveillance and intervention. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.RO (Robotics), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves image processing and computer vision techniques for creating priority maps, which makes cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper also deals with the representation of landscapes and wind conditions, which falls under the sub-category of cs.GR (Graphics).
